@node @code{files-extras-new-empty-buffer-major-mode}
@section @code{files-extras-new-empty-buffer-major-mode}

@vindex files-extras-new-empty-buffer-major-mode
The user option @code{files-extras-new-empty-buffer-major-mode} specifies the
major mode to activate when creating a new empty buffer with
@code{files-extras-new-empty-buffer} (@ref{Creating buffers}).

The default value is @code{org-mode}.  It accepts any symbol naming a valid
major mode function.  If set to @code{nil}, the new buffer will use
@code{fundamental-mode}.  You might change this to @code{markdown-mode} or
@code{text-mode} if you prefer a different default for scratch-like buffers.

