@node Buffer information
@section Buffer information

@findex files-extras-get-alternate-buffer
@findex files-extras-get-stem-of-current-buffer
@findex files-extras-buffer-file-name
@findex files-extras-open-buffer-files
@findex files-extras-bollp
The function @code{files-extras-get-alternate-buffer} returns the most
recently used buffer in the current window, respecting the frame's
@code{buffer-predicate}.  It is used internally by
@code{files-extras-switch-to-alternate-buffer} (@ref{Switching buffers}).

The function @code{files-extras-get-stem-of-current-buffer} returns the base
name (without extension or directory) of the current buffer's file.

The function @code{files-extras-buffer-file-name} returns the file name of
the current buffer, adjusting paths that go through the @samp{git-dirs}
directory structure to point to their canonical locations.

The function @code{files-extras-open-buffer-files} returns a list of all
@samp{.org} files currently open in Emacs buffers.

The function @code{files-extras-bollp} returns @code{t} if point is at the
beginning of the last line in the buffer.

@node File operations
@section File operations

@findex files-extras-read-file
@findex files-extras-newest-file
@findex files-extras-lines-to-list
@findex files-extras-list-to-lines
@findex files-extras-get-help-file
@findex files-extras-get-nth-directory
@findex files-extras-get-current-dir-lowercased
The function @code{files-extras-read-file} prompts for a file path with a
context-aware default: the file at point in Dired, the current buffer's
file, or an explicit FILE argument.

The function @code{files-extras-newest-file} returns the path of the most
recently modified file in a directory, excluding @samp{.DS_Store} and
@samp{.localized} files (common macOS clutter).

The function @code{files-extras-lines-to-list} reads a file and returns its
lines as a list of strings.  The function @code{files-extras-list-to-lines}
performs the inverse operation, writing a list to a file with one element
per line.

The function @code{files-extras-get-help-file} searches for a documentation
file (@samp{.org} or @samp{.md}) corresponding to the given source file, looking
in @samp{doc/} and @samp{docs/} subdirectories.

The function @code{files-extras-get-nth-directory} extracts the Nth path
component from a directory path.

The function @code{files-extras-get-current-dir-lowercased} returns the base
name of the current directory, lowercased, with hyphens replaced by
underscores.

@node Mode and buffer switching
@section Mode and buffer switching

@findex files-extras-switch-to-most-recent-buffer-in-mode
The function @code{files-extras-switch-to-most-recent-buffer-in-mode}
switches to the most recently used buffer whose major mode derives from
the given MODE@.

@node Package management
@section Package management

@findex files-extras-open-elpaca-package
@findex files-extras-open-extras-package
The function @code{files-extras-open-elpaca-package} opens the main Elisp
file for a named Elpaca-managed package by constructing the path within
the Elpaca repos directory.

The function @code{files-extras-open-extras-package} prompts (with
completion) for a file in the @samp{emacs/extras/} directory and opens it.
It is used by the @code{files-extras-dispatch} menu.

@node Process support
@section Process support

@findex files-extras-ocr-pdf-process-filter
The function @code{files-extras-ocr-pdf-process-filter} is a process filter
for @samp{ocrmypdf} output.  It translates raw process output into
human-readable status messages and suppresses duplicates.  For example,
it informs the user when OCR has already been performed and a prefix
argument is needed to force re-processing.

@node Trash and auto-save support
@section Trash and auto-save support

@findex files-extras-system-move-file-to-trash
@findex files-extras-bury-scratch-buffer
@findex files-extras-auto-save-alert
@findex files-extras-make-hashed-auto-save-file-name-a
@findex files-extras-make-hashed-backup-file-name-a
The function @code{files-extras-system-move-file-to-trash} overrides
@code{system-move-file-to-trash} (via @samp{:override} advice) to use the
external @samp{trash} utility on macOS@.  This preserves Finder's ``Put Back''
functionality, which the default Emacs trash implementation does not
support.

The function @code{files-extras-bury-scratch-buffer} is added to
@code{kill-buffer-query-functions}.  It intercepts attempts to kill the
@samp{*scratch*} buffer and buries it instead, returning @code{nil} to prevent the
kill.

The function @code{files-extras-auto-save-alert} is added to
@code{find-file-hook}.  When auto-save data is newer than the visited file,
it triggers a high-severity alert (via the @samp{alert} package) to ensure
the notification is not missed.

The function @code{files-extras-make-hashed-auto-save-file-name-a} advises
@code{make-auto-save-file-name} (@samp{:around}) to hash the buffer file name,
preventing excessively long auto-save file paths.  Similarly,
@code{files-extras-make-hashed-backup-file-name-a} advises
@code{make-backup-file-name-1} to hash backup file names in directories
specified by @code{backup-directory-alist}.

